Perfect! Now I have enough information to provide a comprehensive report. Let me compile all the findings.

## Summary: OpenClaw Channel Plugin Structure

I've thoroughly explored the OpenClaw repository and documented the complete structure of existing channel plugins. Here's what I found:

---

## **Directory Structure of Channel Plugins**

Channel plugins live in `/extensions/{channel-id}/` with this standard layout:

### **IRC Plugin**: `/extensions/irc/`
```
extensions/irc/
├── package.json                    # npm package metadata
├── openclaw.plugin.json            # plugin manifest
├── index.ts                        # main entry point
├── api.ts                          # public API barrel
├── channel-config-api.ts           # config schema export
├── setup-entry.ts                  # setup-only entry point
├── runtime-api.ts                  # runtime barrel (private)
└── src/
    ├── channel.ts                  # ChannelPlugin implementation
    ├── runtime.ts                  # runtime store setup
    ├── types.ts                    # IRC-specific types
    ├── config-schema.ts            # zod-based config schema
    ├── config-ui-hints.ts          # UI hints for config fields
    ├── accounts.ts                 # account resolution logic
    ├── setup-core.ts               # setup adapter impl
